                        <placeName key="place_108937">Sherborne St John (Hampshire)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_111716">Bramley (Hampshire)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116029">Pamber (Hampshire)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_116032">Tadley (Hampshire)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_108136">Basing (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1692">4 William and Mary. Sept. 1, 1692</origDate>. Indenture made between (1) Dame Jane Gardiner of St. Martin in the Fields,
                        Middlesex, widdow, (2) Sir Brocas Gardiner of Roch Court, Hampshire,
                        baronet, son and heir of Dame Jane, and (3) Bernard Gardiner, Fellow of All
                        Souls College, Oxford, gent., being a release from (1) to (2) of lands in
                        Sherborne St John alias East Sherbourne and West Sherbourne, Bramley,
                        Pamber, Tadley Mortimer and Basing, Hampshire, from which (2) will pay (3)
                        an annuity during the life of (1) (signed and sealed by Jane Gardiner, ?Sir
                        Brocas Gardiner and Bernard Gardiner).</p>
